#install.packages('ggplot2')
library(ggplot2)
data(cars)
dta<- cars
ggplot(dta,aes(speed,dist))+
  geom_point(shape=1)+
  geom_smooth(method = lm)
## `geom_smooth()` using formula 'y ~ x'

##################### Gr√°ficos de Dispers√£oia√ßa( lm com intervalo de con)###
ggplot(dta,aes(speed,dist))+
  geom_point(shape=1)+
  geom_smooth(method = lm, se=FALSE) 
## `geom_smooth()` using formula 'y ~ x'

# histograma con curva de densidad
ggplot(mpg, aes(x=hwy))+ 
    geom_histogram(aes(y=..density..),      
                   binwidth=2,
                   colour="black", fill="blue") +
    geom_density(alpha=.2, fill="red")#rellenado de la curva de densidad en rojo suave

mpg_subset <- mpg[mpg$manufacturer=="audi" | mpg$manufacturer=="volkswagen",]

  geom_histogram(binwidth=2, alpha=.5, position="identity")

# histogramas intercalados
ggplot(mpg_subset, aes(x=hwy, fill=manufacturer)) +
    geom_histogram(binwidth=2, position="dodge")

# curvas de densidad
ggplot(mpg_subset, aes(x=hwy, fill=manufacturer))+ 
  geom_density()

# curvas de densidad con rellenado transparente
ggplot(mpg_subset, aes(x=hwy, fill=manufacturer))+
  geom_density(alpha=.3)

#polinomios de frecuencias con colores en funci√≥n de un factor

#histogramas m√°s sofisticados
set.seed(6298)
diamonds_small <- diamonds[sample(nrow(diamonds), 1000), ]
ggplot(diamonds_small, aes(price, ..density.., colour = cut))+ 
  geom_freqpoly(binwidth = 1000)

#m√°s opciones, histogramas solapados con distintos colores en funci√≥n de un factor
hist_cut <- ggplot(diamonds_small, aes(x = price, fill = cut))
hist_cut + geom_histogram(binwidth = 1000)

#gr√°ficos de densidad con diferentes factores marcando colores
ggplot(diamonds_small, aes(price, fill = cut))+
  geom_density(alpha = 0.2)

  geom_bar(stat = 'identity',position=position_dodge()) 

#Para obter um gr√°fico de barras de contagens, n√£o mapeie uma vari√°vel para ye use stat="bin"(que √© o padr√£o) em vez de stat="identity":
#cuenta de clientes por d√≠a
ggplot(dtat,aes(x=day))+
  geom_bar(stat='count')

#cuenta de media de  facturas por d√≠a
ggplot(dtat,aes(x=day,y=total_bill))+
  geom_bar(stat = 'summary',fun.y='mean')

datn2 <- datn
datn2$dose <- factor(datn2$dose)

  geom_line() +
  geom_point()

#Tamb√©m √© poss√≠vel criar um gr√°fico de barras quando a vari√°vel √© tratada como categ√≥rica e n√£o num√©rica.

ggplot(data=datn2, aes(x=dose, y=len, fill=supp)) +
  geom_bar(stat="identity", position=position_dodge())

ggplot(data=datn, aes(x=factor(dose), y=len, fill=supp)) +
  geom_bar(stat="identity", position=position_dodge())
